{"text": "5.5 Acceleration at an instant is determined by the force at that instant.", "fibs": ["instant"]}
{"text": "The moment after a stone is dropped out of an accelerated train, it has no horizontal acceleration or force, if air resistance is neglected.", "fibs": ["moment"]}
{"text": "The stone carries no memory of its acceleration with the train a moment ago.", "fibs": ["stone"]}
{"text": "The second law of motion is a local relation which means that force F at a point in space (location of the particle) at a certain instant of time is related to a at that point at that instant.", "fibs": ["law"]}
{"text": "Acceleration here and now is determined by the force here and now, not by any history of the motion of the particle (See Fig.", "fibs": ["Acceleration"]}
