{"text": "In elastic collisions, there is a second condition that the total initial kinetic energy of the system equals the total final kinetic energy (See Chapter 6).", "fibs": ["condition"]}
{"text": "5.8  Equilibrium of a particle
Equilibrium of a particle in mechanics refers to the situation when the net external force on the particle is zero.", "fibs": ["particle"]}
{"text": "*  According to the first law, this means that, the particle is either at rest or in uniform motion.", "fibs": ["law"]}
{"text": "If two forces F1 and F2, act on a particle, equilibrium requires
 F1  = − F2                                                                                                            (5.10)
i.e.", "fibs": ["act"]}
{"text": "the two forces on the particle  must be equal and opposite.", "fibs": ["particle"]}
{"text": "Equilibrium under three concurrent forces F1, F2  and F3 requires that the vector sum of the three forces is zero.", "fibs": ["Equilibrium"]}
{"text": "F1  + F2  + F3  =  0                                                                                                 (5.11)





